# WHAT IT IS
#   `bos` ("balance of satoshis") is the **canonical day-to-day
#   operator CLI for an LND-based Lightning Network routing node**.
#   It is the tool every serious Lightning routing-node operator
#   uses for `bos rebalance`, `bos fees`, `bos report`,
#   `bos accounting`, `bos peers`, `bos forwards`, `bos pay`,
#   `bos probe`, `bos send`, `bos swap`, `bos swap-in`,
#   `bos chain-deposit`, `bos chainfees`, `bos chart-*`,
#   `bos open`, `bos open-balanced-channel`,
#   `bos create-channel-group`, `bos join-channel-group`,
#   `bos create-fanout-group`, `bos fanout`,
#   `bos increase-inbound-liquidity`,
#   `bos increase-outbound-liquidity`, `bos get-inbound-channel`,
#   `bos remove-peer`, `bos telegram` (full Telegram-bot integration),
#   `bos lnurl` (pay / withdraw / channel / auth),
#   `bos credentials`, `bos encrypt` / `bos decrypt`,
#   `bos trade-secret`, `bos services` (KeySend paid-services server),
#   `bos use`, `bos advertise`, `bos triggers`,
#   `bos inbound-channel-rules`, `bos limit-forwarding`,
#   `bos offer-channel-open`, `bos call` (raw LND gRPC),
#   `bos unlock`, `bos autopilot`, `bos nodes` (manage saved nodes),
#   `bos clean-failed-payments`, `bos delete-payments-history`,
#   `bos closed`, `bos connect`, `bos reconnect`, `bos broadcast`,
#   `bos fund`, `bos gift`, `bos transfer`, `bos invoice`,
#   `bos balance`, `bos inbound-liquidity`, `bos outbound-liquidity`,
#   `bos liquidity-cost`, `bos swap-api-key`,
#   `bos change-channel-capacity`, `bos cert-validity-days`,
#   `bos clean-command`, `bos find`, `bos graph`, `bos price`,
#   `bos tags`, `bos utxos`, and `bos open-group-channel`
#   (69 total subcommands).
#
#   Multi-node aware: the `--node <node_name>` option is universal
#   across nearly every subcommand and refers to the entries in
#   `~/.bos/<node_name>/credentials.json` so an operator can drive
#   multiple LND nodes from a single CLI invocation.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from upstream `bos` bin script,
#                       extracted via `gh api repos/alexbosworth/
#                       balanceofsatoshis/contents/bos`; flag set
#                       parsed by `@alexbosworth/caporal` 2.0.0 — a
#                       fork of `caporal`)
#
#   bos <command> [args…] [options…]
#
#   Caporal exposes the standard global auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help (top-level or per-command)
#     -V, --version                  Print version and exit
#     -v, --verbose                  Verbose mode
#     --quiet, --silent              Quiet mode (no output)
#     --no-color                     Disable ANSI colors
#     --color                        Force ANSI colors on
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `balanceofsatoshis` declares a **direct** dependency on
#   `bitcoinjs-lib@^6.1.7` in its `package.json` (verified via
#   `gh api repos/alexbosworth/balanceofsatoshis/contents/
#   package.json`).  `bitcoinjs-lib` is THE canonical pure-JS
#   Bitcoin protocol library — the JS/TS counterpart to
#   rust-bitcoin (Rust) and btcsuite/btcd (Go) — used by
#   essentially every browser Bitcoin wallet, every Node-based
#   Bitcoin tool, every Electrum-compatible web wallet, every
#   PSBT signing GUI, and every BIP-39/BIP-32 mnemonic derivation
#   tool on the modern JS/TS stack (BlueWallet, Sparrow Wallet's
#   web tooling, Trezor Connect, Specter Desktop's web frontend,
#   Caravan, Liquality, Iris Wallet, OneKey, Coldcard's PSBT
#   tools, Samourai's Whirlpool web UI, and dozens of other
#   production Bitcoin wallet and tool projects).  It exposes
#   typed `bitcoin.Transaction` / `bitcoin.TransactionBuilder`
#   (deprecated) / `bitcoin.Psbt` (PSBT BIP-174 implementation
#   with typed `psbt.addInput()`, `psbt.addOutput()`,
#   `psbt.signInput(idx, keypair)`, `psbt.finalizeAllInputs()`,
#   `psbt.extractTransaction()`, `psbt.toHex()`, `psbt.toBase64()`
#   methods), typed `bitcoin.networks.bitcoin` /  `testnet` /
#   `regtest` named network parameter constants, typed
#   `bitcoin.address.fromBase58Check(addr)` /
#   `bitcoin.address.fromBech32(addr)` /
#   `bitcoin.address.toOutputScript(addr, network)` /
#   `bitcoin.address.fromOutputScript(script, network)`
#   address-encoding primitives, typed `bitcoin.payments.p2pkh()`
#   / `payments.p2sh()` / `payments.p2wpkh()` /
#   `payments.p2wsh()` / `payments.p2tr()` / `payments.p2ms()`
#   typed payment-construction builders, typed
#   `bitcoin.script.compile(chunks)` /
#   `bitcoin.script.decompile(buffer)` /
#   `bitcoin.script.toASM(script)` /
#   `bitcoin.script.fromASM(asm)` script primitives, typed
#   `bitcoin.opcodes.OP_DUP` / `OP_HASH160` / `OP_EQUALVERIFY`
#   / `OP_CHECKSIG` / `OP_CHECKMULTISIG` / `OP_IF` / `OP_NOTIF`
#   / `OP_ELSE` / `OP_ENDIF` / `OP_CHECKSEQUENCEVERIFY` /
#   `OP_CHECKLOCKTIMEVERIFY` named opcode constants, typed
#   `bitcoin.crypto.hash160(buf)` / `crypto.hash256(buf)` /
#   `crypto.sha1(buf)` / `crypto.sha256(buf)` / `crypto.ripemd160(buf)`
#   crypto primitives, typed `bitcoin.ECPair` (now factored out
#   into the `ecpair` sister package as `ECPairFactory(tinysecp)`)
#   keypair primitives, typed `bitcoin.bip32` (now factored out
#   into the `bip32` sister package as `BIP32Factory(tinysecp)`)
#   hierarchical-deterministic key derivation, typed
#   `bitcoin.HDNode` (deprecated; replaced by `bip32`), typed
#   `Bufferutils.readUInt64LE(buffer, offset)` / `writeUInt64LE`
#   wire-encoding helpers, the `Block.fromHex(hex)` block
#   deserializer, and the `Transaction.fromHex(hex)` /
#   `Transaction.toHex()` / `tx.getId()` /  `tx.virtualSize()` /
#   `tx.weight()` /  `tx.byteLength()` transaction primitives.
